column2: CAMAY2    <- ggplot(SANTIAGO,aes(x = cluster2,y = CAMAY))        + geom_boxplot() + labs(title = "Numero AD"                                            , x = "Cluster", y = "Cantidad")   + geom_hline(aes(yintercept = mean(CAMAY))    ,linetype="dotted",size=1.5,color="deeppink1")

AMQVS2    <- ggplot(SANTIAGO,aes(x = cluster2,y = AMQVS))        + geom_boxplot() + labs(title = "Numero AD que viven solos"                            , x = "Cluster", y = "Cantidad")   + geom_hline(aes(yintercept = mean(AMQVS))    ,linetype="dotted",size=1.5,color="deeppink1")

PAMQVS2   <- ggplot(SANTIAGO,aes(x = cluster2,y = PAMQVS))       + geom_boxplot() + labs(title = "Porcentaje AD que viven solos"                        , x = "Cluster", y = "Porcentaje") + geom_hline(aes(yintercept = mean(PAMQVS))   ,linetype="dotted",size=1.5,color="deeppink1")

PAMQTRA2  <- ggplot(SANTIAGO,aes(x = cluster2,y = PAMQTRA))      + geom_boxplot() + labs(title = "Porcentaje AD que trabajan"                           , x = "Cluster", y = "Cantidad")   + geom_hline(aes(yintercept = mean(PAMQTRA))  ,linetype="dotted",size=1.5,color="deeppink1")

PAMJUBI2  <- ggplot(SANTIAGO,aes(x = cluster2,y = PAMJUBI))      + geom_boxplot() + labs(title = "Porcentaje AD jubilados"                              , x = "Cluster", y = "Cantidad")   + geom_hline(aes(yintercept = mean(PAMJUBI))  ,linetype="dotted",size=1.5,color="deeppink1")
